library(tidyr)
library(dplyr)

nd_look <- read_csv("north_dakota.csv")
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   `Apple Creek` = col_character(),
##   Industrial = col_character(),
##   Year = col_character(),
##   `Acre Feet` = col_character(),
##   Acres = col_character()
## )
north_dakota <- read_csv("north_dakota.csv") %>% 
  clean_names() %>% 
  select(-acres) %>% 
  filter(!grepl('Acre Feet', acre_feet)) #!grepl excludes all 'Acre Feet' observations from acre_feet column
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   `Apple Creek` = col_character(),
##   Industrial = col_character(),
##   Year = col_character(),
##   `Acre Feet` = col_character(),
##   Acres = col_character()
## )
north_dakota <- north_dakota %>% 
  rename(basin_name = apple_creek)

north_dakota <- north_dakota %>% 
  rename(use_type = industrial)

north_dakota$acre_feet <- as.numeric(north_dakota$acre_feet) #changing from classifying as character to numeric


# grouping by basin
nd_basin <- north_dakota %>% 
  group_by(basin_name, year) %>% 
  summarize(use_af = sum(acre_feet))

ggplot(nd_basin,
       aes(x = year,
           y = use_af)) +
  geom_line(aes(color = basin_name)) +
  theme(legend.position = "none")
## geom_path: Each group consists of only one observation. Do you need to adjust
## the group aesthetic?

# statewide data
nd_state <- nd_basin %>% 
  group_by(year) %>% 
  summarize(use_af = sum(use_af))

ggplot(nd_state,
       aes(x = year,
           y = use_af)) +
  geom_point()

nd_2 <- read_csv("north_dakota_2.csv") %>% 
    clean_names() %>% 
  select(-acres) %>% 
  filter(!grepl('Acre Feet', acre_feet)) %>% 
  select(-(5:7))
## Warning: Missing column names filled in: 'X6' [6], 'X7' [7], 'X8' [8]
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   `Apple Creek` = col_character(),
##   Domestic = col_character(),
##   Year = col_character(),
##   `Acre Feet` = col_character(),
##   Acres = col_character(),
##   X6 = col_logical(),
##   X7 = col_logical(),
##   X8 = col_logical()
## )
nd_2 <- nd_2 %>% 
  rename(basin_name = apple_creek)

nd_2 <- nd_2 %>% 
  rename(use_type = domestic)

nd_2$acre_feet <- as.numeric(nd_2$acre_feet) #changing from classifying as character to numeric
nd_2$year <- as.numeric(nd_2$year)

# grouping by basin
nd_2_basin <- nd_2 %>% 
  group_by(basin_name, year) %>% 
  summarize(use_af = sum(acre_feet))

ggplot(nd_2_basin,
       aes(x = year,
           y = use_af)) +
  geom_line(aes(color = basin_name)) +
  theme(legend.position = "none")

# statewide data
nd_2_state <- nd_2_basin %>% 
  group_by(year) %>% 
  summarize(use_af = sum(use_af))

ggplot(nd_2_state,
       aes(x = year,
           y = use_af)) +
  geom_line()
